This paper is primarily focused on multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL), which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with distributed decision making, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses practical case studies, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
